---

## ğŸ›  Installation

### Clone and build

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/terminal-assistant.git
cd terminal-assistant
make build
mv bin/bff ~/.local/bin/
echo 'export PATH="$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH"' >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc
```

### Set environment variables

```bash
export OLLAMA_URL=http://localhost:11434
export OLLAMA_MODEL=llama3.2
```

---

## ğŸ“ Usage

Ask a general terminal question:
```bash
bff -q "How do I list all files including hidden ones?"
```

Ask for a command suggestion:
```bash
bff -c "List all .go files recursively"
```

### Flags

| Flag         | Alias | Description                                 |
| ------------ | ----- | ------------------------------------------- |
| `--command`  | `-c`  | Ask for a bash command suggestion           |
| `--question` | `-q`  | Ask a general terminal or shell question    |
| `--help`     | `-h`  | Show help message (auto-generated by Cobra) |

